description: Every single year, approximately 3 to 4 million dogs and cats lose their lives in animal shelters simply because there aren't enough homes for them all!

Breeders kill shelter animals' chances, meaning that for every puppy or kitten who is purchased from a breeder, an animal at a shelter loses his or her chance at finding a loving home.

But these lives appear to mean nothing to Instagram, as the social-media company has refused to ban the sale of dogs, cats, and other animals on its website.

Online sales of animals make it impossible to make sure that vulnerable animals are headed to responsible, loving homes, where they will receive proper veterinary, physical, and social care. Ads tend to appeal to impulse buyers who do not give serious thought to the lifelong commitment needed to provide animals with the stability that they deserve.

Amazon, Craigslist, and eBay have all made the compassionate decision to ban the sale of cats, dogs, and some other live animals online. Instagram should be next!

